          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  The main results from both reaction",
                "channels  already  published are briefly recalled:",
                "the total fission cross section for all elements",
                "between nitrogen and rhenium, (1.53+/-0.15) B, is more",
                "than 3 times larger than the evaporation residues cross",
                "section, (0.44+/-0.06) B.  Evaporation residues -",
                "production is the main source of fragments close to  U.",
                "After a rapid fall, within the 10 mass units close to U",
                "covering 0.24 B (the main part of the evaporation",
                "residues cross section) the mass distribution decreases",
                "smoothly from 5 mb to 4 mb within a range of mass",
                "losses of 45 mass units.  Finally a break-down by a",
                "factor of 5 to the level of 0.8 mb is observed at a",
                "mass loss of 70, where the evaporation residues-cross",
                "sections equal the fission fragments cross sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A thin liquid hidrogen target (87 mg/cm2)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Forward emitted fragments, bare from atomic",
                "electrons, are analysed in momentum with the high-",
                "resolution fragment separator and fully identified in",
                "the associated detectors;  time-of-flight and energy",
                "loss of ions were measured.",
                "The velocity of each fragment is precisely determined",
                "and converted into the rest frame of the projectile.",
                "The velocity distribution for a given nuclide reveals",
                "the process from where it comes:  either from fission",
                "of a more or less excited spallation residue leading to",
                "two fission fragments , or from evaporation of nucleons",
                "leading to evaporation residues."
              ]
            }
          ],
